                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12970316" author="mingjielai" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 21:29:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A WAL coprocessor (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3257&quot; title=&quot;Coprocessors: Extend server side integration API to include HLog operations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3257&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3257&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) can help to solve the problem. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By a WAL cp implementation, one or multiple specified columns can be removed from the passed WALEdit before appending to WAL, so that they will be ignored at WAL. However they will still be written to store files. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another option is to utilize existing WALObserver which provides a hook to insert user code before HLog.doWrite(). But currently it doesn&apos;t support to modify the passed WALEdit. I think Coprocessor is a better way to do it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970339" author="karthik.ranga" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 23:35:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, a co-processors based implementation would totally work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12978929" author="kannanm" created="Fri, 7 Jan 2011 19:30:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One workaround would be to use:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Put.writeToWAL(false). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caveat: This wouldn&apos;t work for the case when you have a mix of column families in the Put, some of which you want to write to WAL and others you don&apos;t. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989347" author="mingjielai" created="Tue, 1 Feb 2011 19:32:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Karthik. &lt;br/&gt;
Please take a look at the patch at reviewboard for HBase-3257 &amp;#8211; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.cloudera.org/r/1515/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://review.cloudera.org/r/1515/&lt;/a&gt;. There is a SampleRegionWALObserver which can add, remove, modify KeyValues to a WALEdit before written to WAL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14021447" author="apurtell" created="Sun, 8 Jun 2014 22:04:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stale issue. Reopen if still relevant (if there&apos;s new activity)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
